Lagos State Commissioner for Education, Mrs Folasade Adefisayo, has advised students to always pay attention to the instructions of their parents and teachers. Adefisayo, at the 15th merit award of the Lagos State Education District IV, Sabo, Yaba, encouraged the awardees for their good work. She said the reward for hard work was more work, adding that the workers needed to strive more for efficient service delivery to the district The commissioner was represented by the Director, Child Guidance and School Counseling, Special Education Unit, Ministry of Education, Mrs Olusola Somoye. The event, which was held at Sanya Senior Grammar School, Surulere, was titled, ‘Resilient Achievers In the face of Daunting Challenges.’ The Tutor General/Permanent Secretary, Education District IV, Mr Charles Olajide, said the annual programme was held to encourage workers for their excellent performance. “The characteristics for selection of schools are based on academic performance in WASSCE, NECO.  We also looked at workers’ punctuality to school, their impact on students and the school in general,” he said. Olajide also received an award for his unflinching support for the development of education in Lagos State at the event. Awards were also presented to the best school, teachers, principals, students and non-teaching staff of the district. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com